title: tract10 125v12b
name: tract10 125v12b
description: The following field definitions make up the county based shapefile attribute table called Census 2010 Tracts. The attribute table can be found in the file tract10_999v12b.DBF where 999 equals the FIPS county number contained in the file. The FIPS county numbering system uses odd numbers only. The numbers are assigned in alphabetical order. For example, county 001 is Alcona and county 165 is Wexford. The attributes describe the data attached to polygons that represent U.S. Census 2010 tract boundaries as assigned to the Michigan Geographic Framework (MGF).
